    {
      "id": "b-002",
      "mode": "explain",
      "speakerNote": "Warm, personal. Tell your real story about getting lost in Bangkok. Make it relatable and funny.",
      "imageRef": "img-001",
      "lines": [
        {
          "id": "l-0004",
          "lang": "en",
          "english": "My first week in Bangkok, I got completely lost trying to find a BTS station. The signs were all in Thai, my phone was dead, and I was sweating in 35-degree heat. I stopped an old lady and just said 'BTS?' with a confused face. She laughed, grabbed my arm, and walked me there herself. Thai people are incredibly kind — but it's so much better when you can actually ask properly.",
          "display": "immediate",
          "spoken": true
        },
        {
          "id": "l-0005",
          "lang": "th",
          "thai": "ขอโทษค่ะ สถานีรถไฟฟ้าอยู่ที่ไหนคะ",
          "translit": "khǎaw-thôot khâ sa-thǎa-nii rót-fai-fáa yùu thîi nǎi khá",
          "display": "immediate",
          "spoken": true
        },
        {
          "id": "l-0006",
          "lang": "en",
          "english": "By the end of this video, you'll know how to ask where anything is — and understand directions like 'go straight' and 'turn left'.",
          "display": "immediate",
          "spoken": true
        }
      ]
    },
